{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778376997689,"sessionID":"ses_1f07899b5ffeFiIzq6p620aHwD","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_rnXEa9pwNyIhahxnrJxaq1EW","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/__issue_context__.json","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/__issue_context__.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"body\": \"There is currently this tree:\\n\\n```\\ndiamine oxidase activity [EC:1.4.3.22 {source=\\\"skos:broadMatch\\\"}]\\n   |__histamine oxidase activity [EC:1.4.3.22 {source=\\\"skos:broadMatch\\\"}]\\n   |__putrescine oxidase activity [EC:1.4.3.10 {source=\\\"skos:exactMatch\\\"}]\\n   |__protein-lysine 6-oxidase activity [EC:1.4.3.13 {source=\\\"skos:exactMatch\\\"}]\\n```\\n\\nEC:1.4.3.22 is:\\nReaction catalysed: histamine + O2 + H2O = imidazole-4-acetaldehyde + H2O2 + NH4(+)\\nComments: A group of enzymes that oxidize diamines, such as histamine, and also some primary monoamines but have little or no activity toward secondary and tertiary amines.\\n\\nAlso, protein-lysine 6-oxidase activity is not a 'diamine oxidase activity'.\\n\\nSo:\\n- [x] Remove  EC:1.4.3.22 {source=\\\"skos:broadMatch\\\"} from 'histamine oxidase activity' and leave as broadMatch on parent 'diamine oxidase activity'\\n- [x] change parent of protein-lysine 6-oxidase activity to 'GO:0016641 oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-NH2 group of donors, oxygen as acceptor' (=EC:1.4.3.-)\",\n3:   \"comments\": [],\n4:   \"title\": \"GO:0052597 diamine oxidase activity terms\",\n5:   \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31964\"\n6: }\n\n(End of file - total 6 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"body\": \"There is currently this tree:\\n\\n```\\ndiamine oxidase activity [EC:1.4.3.22 {source=\\\"skos:broadMatch\\\"}]\\n   |__histamine oxidase activity [EC:1.4.3.22 {source=\\\"skos:broadMatch\\\"}]\\n   |__putrescine oxidase activity [EC:1.4.3.10 {source=\\\"skos:exactMatch\\\"}]\\n   |__protein-lysine 6-oxidase activity [EC:1.4.3.13 {source=\\\"skos:exactMatch\\\"}]\\n```\\n\\nEC:1.4.3.22 is:\\nReaction catalysed: histamine + O2 + H2O = imidazole-4-acetaldehyde + H2O2 + NH4(+)\\nComments: A group of enzymes that oxidize diamines, such as histamine, and also some primary monoamines but have little or no activity toward secondary and tertiary amines.\\n\\nAlso, protein-lysine 6-oxidase activity is not a 'diamine oxidase activity'.\\n\\nSo:\\n- [x] Remove  EC:1.4.3.22 {source=\\\"skos:broadMatch\\\"} from 'histamine oxidase activity' and leave as broadMatch on parent 'diamine oxidase activity'\\n- [x] change parent of protein-lysine 6-oxidase activity to 'GO:0016641 oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-NH2 group of donors, oxygen as acceptor' (=EC:1.4.3.-)\",\n  \"comments\": [],\n  \"title\": \"GO:0052597 diamine oxidase activity terms\",\n  \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31964\"\n}","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"__issue_context__.json","time":{"start":1778376997637,"end":1778376997687}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_093e333842e85b020169ffe12581d881a0afd7c6ffa621c3df"}},"id":"prt_e0f877ac7001F9GKsfrZtlsEmt","sessionID":"ses_1f07899b5ffeFiIzq6p620aHwD","messageID":"msg_e0f87670200117zC24L4sY9bKs"}}
