llagen and elastin cross-linking in the biosynthesis of normal mature extracellular matrices.\n-   These reactions play an important role for the development, elasticity and extensibility of connective tissue.\n-   Also active on free amines, such as cadaverine or benzylamine.\n\nCross-references\n\nRhea expert-curated reactions\n\n[1.4.3.13](https://www.rhea-db.org/rhea?query=ec%3A1.4.3.13)\n\nExplorEnz\n\n[1.4.3.13](http://www.enzyme-database.org/query.php?ec=1.4.3.13)\n\nIUBMB Enzyme Nomenclature\n\n[1.4.3.13](https://www.qmul.ac.uk/sbcs/iubmb/enzyme/EC1/4/3/13.html)\n\nUniProtKB/Swiss-Prot\n\n[F1QQC3](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/F1QQC3), LOL2A\\_DANRE\n\n[A1L1V4](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/A1L1V4), LOL2B\\_DANRE\n\n[F1RD85](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/F1RD85), LOX3A\\_DANRE\n\n[B8A4W9](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/B8A4W9), LOX3B\\_DANRE\n\n[Q95L39](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q95L39), LOXL1\\_BOVIN\n\n[Q08397](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q08397), LOXL1\\_HUMAN\n\n[P97873](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P97873), LOXL1\\_MOUSE\n\n[A6H737](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/A6H737), LOXL2\\_BOVIN\n\n[E1C3U7](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/E1C3U7), LOXL2\\_CHICK\n\n[Q9Y4K0](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q9Y4K0), LOXL2\\_HUMAN\n\n[P58022](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P58022), LOXL2\\_MOUSE\n\n[Q5RFQ6](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q5RFQ6), LOXL2\\_PONAB\n\n[B5DF27](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/B5DF27), LOXL2\\_RAT\n\n[Q08B63](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q08B63), LOXL2\\_XENLA\n\n[B4F6N6](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/B4F6N6), LOXL2\\_XENTR\n\n[P58215](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P58215), LOXL3\\_HUMAN\n\n[Q9Z175](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q9Z175), LOXL3\\_MOUSE\n\n[Q8MJ24](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q8MJ24), LOXL4\\_BOVIN\n\n[Q96JB6](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q96JB6), LOXL4\\_HUMAN\n\n[Q924C6](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q924C6), LOXL4\\_MOUSE\n\n[P33072](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P33072), LYOX\\_B