on catalysed\n\nhistamine + O2 + H2O = imidazole-4-acetaldehyde + H2O2 + NH4(+)\n\nComment(s)\n\n-   A group of enzymes that oxidize diamines, such as histamine, and also some primary monoamines but have little or no activity toward secondary and tertiary amines.\n-   They are copper quinoproteins (2,4,5-trihydroxyphenylalanine quinone) and, like EC [1.4.3.21](/EC/1.4.3.21) but unlike EC [1.4.3.4](/EC/1.4.3.4), they are sensitive to inhibition by carbonyl-group reagents, such as semicarbazide.\n-   Formerly EC 1.4.3.6.\n\nCross-references\n\nRhea expert-curated reactions\n\n[1.4.3.22](https://www.rhea-db.org/rhea?query=ec%3A1.4.3.22)\n\nExplorEnz\n\n[1.4.3.22](http://www.enzyme-database.org/query.php?ec=1.4.3.22)\n\nIUBMB Enzyme Nomenclature\n\n[1.4.3.22](https://www.qmul.ac.uk/sbcs/iubmb/enzyme/EC1/4/3/22.html)\n\nUniProtKB/Swiss-Prot\n\n[Q12556](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q12556), AMO1\\_ASPNG\n\n[Q59118](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q59118), AMOH\\_ARTGO\n\n[P19801](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P19801), AOC1\\_HUMAN\n\n[Q8JZQ5](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q8JZQ5), AOC1\\_MOUSE\n\n[Q9TRC7](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q9TRC7), AOC1\\_PIG\n\n[P36633](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P36633), AOC1\\_RAT\n\nBRENDA\n\n[1.4.3.22](http://www.brenda-enzymes.org/enzyme.php?ecno=1.4.3.22)\n\nMetaCyc\n\n[1.4.3.22](https://biocyc.org/META/NEW-IMAGE?type=EC-NUMBER&object=EC-1.4.3.22)\n\nKEGG Ligand Database for Enzyme Nomenclature\n\n[1.4.3.22](http://www.genome.ad.jp/dbget-bin/www_bget?ec:1.4.3.22)\n\nMEDLINE\n\n[Find literature relating to 1.4.3.22](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=PureSearch&db=PubMed&details_term=1.4.3.22[EC/RN%20Number])\n\n  \n[View entry in original ENZYME format](/cgi-bin/enzyme/get-enzyme-entry?1.4.3.22)  \n[View entry in raw text format (no links)](/EC/1.4.3.22.txt)  \n\n[All UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot entries referenced in this entry](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb?query=\\(ec:1.4.3.22\\)%20AND%20\\(reviewed:true\\))